<subSubSection id="C30E653FC66BA219F53DF882F4C84A5A" pageId="29" pageNumber="256" type="reference_group">
<paragraph id="8BAB36B4C66BA219F53DF882F4DD44EF" blockId="29.[2755,3562,1816,2385]" pageId="29" pageNumber="256">
<emphasis id="B960EAA6C66BA219F53DF882F4774479" bold="true" box="[2757,2968,1816,1855]" pageId="29" pageNumber="256">Taxonomy.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C144D37C66BA219F408F882F3FC4432" authority="G. S. Miller, 1902" authorityName="G. S. Miller" authorityYear="1902" class="Mammalia" family="Hipposideridae" genus="Hipposideros" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="29" pageNumber="256" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="nicobarulae">Hipposideros nicobarulae G. S. Miller, 1902</taxonomicName>
, 
<materialsCitation id="3B7C3CE9C66BA219F3D2F8D7F20A4432" ID-GBIF-Occurrence="3753598311" box="[3114,3557,1869,1908]" pageId="29" pageNumber="256">“Little Nicobar Island,”</materialsCitation>
<collectingCountry id="F3037624C66BA219F53DF818F4C344EF" box="[2757,2860,1922,1961]" name="India" pageId="29" pageNumber="256">India</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BAB36B4C66BA219F53EF82DF4C84A5A" blockId="29.[2755,3562,1816,2385]" pageId="29" pageNumber="256">
<taxonomicName id="4C144D37C66BA219F53EF82DF3904498" authorityName="G. S. Miller" authorityYear="1902" box="[2758,3199,1975,2014]" class="Mammalia" family="Hipposideridae" genus="Hipposideros" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="29" pageNumber="256" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="nicobarulae">Hipposideros nicobarulae</taxonomicName>
is in the 
<taxonomicName id="4C144D37C66BA219F2B3F82DF2604498" authorityName="Templeton" authorityYear="1848" box="[3403,3471,1975,2014]" class="Mammalia" family="Hipposideridae" genus="Hipposideros" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="29" pageNumber="256" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="ater">ater</taxonomicName>
species group, and was previously considered a subspecies of 
<taxonomicName id="4C144D37C66BA219F40BF7BBF39B4B0E" authorityName="Templeton" authorityYear="1848" box="[3059,3188,2081,2120]" class="Mammalia" family="Hipposideridae" genus="Hipposideros" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="29" pageNumber="256" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="ater">H. ater</taxonomicName>
. Based on detailed morphometric and craniodental studies, it was raised to species level by B. Douangboubpha and colleagues in 2011. Monotypic.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C30E653FC66BA219F53DF6B0F2E64A17" box="[2757,3337,2346,2385]" pageId="29" pageNumber="256" type="multiple">
