<subSubSection id="C30E653FC66BA219F875F6C5F5B7491C" pageId="29" pageNumber="256" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BAB36B4C66BA219F875F6C5F5B7491C" blockId="29.[1931,3557,2399,3174]" pageId="29" pageNumber="256">
<emphasis id="B960EAA6C66BA219F875F6C5F70F4AC0" bold="true" box="[1933,2272,2399,2438]" pageId="29" pageNumber="256">Descriptive notes.</emphasis>
Ear 15-19 mm, forearm 38-42 mm. Noseleaf of the Nicobar Leafnosed Bat is without lateral supplementary leaflet. Anterior leaf has deep emargination. Intemarial septum is swollen, broader at base and narrower at tip. Rostrum is inflated but only moderately. P2 is small and extruded. Baculum is very small, with a curved shaft and simple base and tips.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
